  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious financial crime. It involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other criminal enterprises) appear to be legally earned. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate\n\nMoney laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nIt's a federal crime in the United States and many other countries, with severe legal consequences.",
